), relative rostral height (50.1 versus 53.2–65.5), relative frontonasal length (2.46 versus 2.95–3.65), and the relative interparietal distance (0.632 versus 0–0.435). From 
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCEFFE90DBA0F21070FD0E8" box="[220,347,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFCEFFE90DBA0F210703D0E8" authority="Cope, 1861" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1861" baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[220,343,1910,1936]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Panolopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Panolopus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
we distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFCEFFE90F760F21043BD0E8" authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[528,623,1910,1936]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCEFFE90F760F21043BD0E8" box="[528,623,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Advenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCEFFE90F110F2104B5D0E8" bold="true" box="[631,737,1910,1936]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7B886A6FFFCEFFE90F110F2104B5D0E8" box="[631,737,1910,1936]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the claw sheath (present versus its absence in 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFCEFFE9087D0F2103C7D0E8" authority="Cope, 1861" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1861" baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[1307,1427,1910,1936]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" genus="Panolopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCEFFE9087D0F2103C7D0E8" box="[1307,1427,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Panolopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the relative axilla-groin distance (60.0 versus 49.7–59.6). From 
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCEFFE90EF40FCD05AED0CC" box="[914,1018,1946,1972]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFCEFFE90EF40FCD05A2D0CC" authority="Gray, 1852" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1852" box="[914,1014,1946,1972]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Sauresia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Sauresia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
we distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFCEFFE909CC0FCD035DD0CC" authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[1194,1289,1946,1972]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCEFFE909CC0FCD035DD0CC" box="[1194,1289,1946,1972]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Advenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCEFFE908760FCD032DD0CC" bold="true" box="[1296,1401,1946,1972]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7B886A6FFFCEFFE908760FCD032DD0CC" box="[1296,1401,1946,1972]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the digits per limb (five versus four), the longest toe lamellae (16–17 versus 8–12), the dorsal scale rows (96 versus 101–127), the relative interparietal distance (0.632 versus 0–0.431), and the relative axilla-groin distance (60.0 versus 63.9–69.9). From 
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCFFFE80CC908EC0460D7AC" box="[431,564,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFCFFFE80CC908EC047BD7AC" authority="Cochran, 1927" authorityName="Cochran" authorityYear="1927" box="[431,559,187,212]" class="Lepidosauria" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Wetmorena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Wetmorena</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
we distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFCFFFE80F8408EC0515D7AD" authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[738,833,187,213]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCFFFE80F8408EC0515D7AD" box="[738,833,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Advenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCFFFE80E2E08EC05E4D7AD" bold="true" box="[840,944,187,213]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7B886A6FFFCFFFE80E2E08EC05E4D7AD" box="[840,944,187,213]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the digits per limb (five versus four), the number of longest toe lamellae (16–17 versus 8–12), and the dorsal scale rows (96 versus 98–117).
</paragraph>
