<paragraph id="52700B06FFCFFFE80DA10B95051CD4A4" blockId="17.[151,1437,962,1348]" box="[199,840,962,989]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCFFFE80DA10B95077BD4A4" bold="true" box="[199,303,962,988]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Content.</emphasis>
One species (
<tableCitation id="1F4D3EBDFFCFFFE80CAD0B950475D4A5" box="[459,545,962,989]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="14.[151,239,1291,1315]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,1404,2011]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="TABLE 3. Classification and distribution of lizards of the family Diploglossidae (55 species). For common names we use modifying words from literature sources, in some cases modified for consistency following guidelines (Hedges et al. 2019). The IUCN Redlist threat status is indicated in parentheses (NA = not assessed)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/06B05B8EFFD0FFF70DF10D5C0264D214" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" tableUuid="06B05B8EFFD0FFF70DF10D5C0264D214">Table 3</tableCitation>
): 
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCFFFE80F510B95051CD4A4" box="[567,840,962,988]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFCFFFE80F510B950510D4A4" baseAuthorityName="Myers" baseAuthorityYear="1973" box="[567,836,962,988]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montisilvestris">Advenus montisilvestris</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1AD5588DFFCFFFE80DA10BB106AED331" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="52700B06FFCFFFE80DA10BB106AED331" blockId="17.[151,1437,962,1348]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCFFFE80DA10BB10735D378" bold="true" box="[199,353,998,1024]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known from only 
<specimenCount id="44C9C08FFFCFFFE80F270BB00489D378" box="[577,733,998,1025]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
collected on the southeastern slope of Cerro Pirre (
<quantity id="9537A6E3FFCFFFE808550BB003DBD379" box="[1331,1423,999,1025]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.44" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" unit="m" value="1440.0">1440 m</quantity>
), Serranía de Pirre, Province of 
<collectingRegion id="900BC5E4FFCFFFE80C930C5D0410D35C" box="[501,580,1034,1060]" country="Panama" name="Darien" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Darién</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="2AD84B96FFCFFFE80F370C5D056DD35D" box="[593,825,1034,1061]" name="Panama" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Republic of Panama</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="CAF41783FFCFFFE80E2C0C5D05C5D35D" box="[842,913,1034,1061]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="17.[151,250,892,916]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,273,869]" captionTargetId="figure-65@17.[151,1436,273,869]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 7. The distribution of Advenus gen. nov. in southeastern Panama, near the border with Colombia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775462" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775462/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). By our calculation, the location is 
<geoCoordinate id="37FB6DC1FFCFFFE808500C5C03D2D35D" box="[1334,1414,1035,1061]" degrees="7.9242" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" precision="5" value="7.9242">7.9242</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="37FB6DC1FFCFFFE808F50C5C06A2D331" degrees="77.7000" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" precision="5" value="-77.7">- 77.7000</geoCoordinate>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1AD5588DFFCFFFE80DA10C04031AD3E8" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="52700B06FFCFFFE80DA10C04031AD3E8" blockId="17.[151,1437,962,1348]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCFFFE80DA10C04071AD315" bold="true" box="[199,334,1107,1133]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFCFFFE80F7D0C05042ED314" authority="Caribicus" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[539,634,1106,1132]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="243" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCFFFE80F7D0C05042ED314" box="[539,634,1106,1132]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Advenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a masculine noun derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCFFFE809320C0502F1D314" box="[1108,1189,1106,1132]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">advena</emphasis>
(“stranger”), referring to the distribution of this species in Middle America when all of its close relatives are on Caribbean islands.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1AD5588DFFCFFFE80DA10CCC0211D23C" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="52700B06FFCFFFE80DA10CCC0211D23C" blockId="17.[151,1437,962,1348]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCFFFE80DA10CCC076FD3CD" bold="true" box="[199,315,1179,1205]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFCFFFE80C240CCD0418D3CC" baseAuthorityName="Myers" baseAuthorityYear="1973" box="[322,588,1178,1204]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montisilvestris">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCFFFE80C240CCD0418D3CC" box="[322,588,1178,1204]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Advenus montisilvestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only member of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFCFFFE80E920CCD023DD3CC" authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[1012,1129,1178,1204]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" status="subfam. nov." subFamily="Celestinae">Celestinae</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCFFFE809160CCD035CD3CD" bold="true" box="[1136,1288,1178,1205]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7B886A6FFFCFFFE809160CCD035CD3CD" box="[1136,1288,1178,1205]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" rank="subFamily">subfam. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
that is found outside of the Caribbean. The name 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFCFFFE80F4B0CE90484D3A0" baseAuthorityName="Myers" baseAuthorityYear="1973" box="[557,720,1214,1240]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montisilvestris">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCFFFE80F4B0CE90484D3A0" box="[557,720,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">montisilvestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the mountain forest at the 
<typeStatus id="8D74B5A4FFCFFFE809390CE802DBD3A1" box="[1119,1167,1215,1241]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">type</typeStatus>
locality. Morphological traits align this species with the other members of 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFCFFFE80F8B0CB50536D384" authority="Schools &amp; Hedges, 2021" authorityName="Schools &amp; Hedges" authorityYear="2021" box="[749,866,1250,1276]" class="Reptilia" family="Anguidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" status="subfam. nov." subFamily="Celestinae">Celestinae</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCFFFE80E0B0CB5025CD385" bold="true" box="[877,1032,1250,1277]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7B886A6FFFCFFFE80E0B0CB5025CD385" box="[877,1032,1250,1277]" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" rank="subFamily">subfam. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
that are distributed in the western Caribbean, on the islands of 
<collectingCountry id="2AD84B96FFCFFFE80C850D510469D258" box="[483,573,1286,1312]" name="Jamaica" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
and Hispaniola, but not with any one genus. Genetic data are necessary to further clarify the relationship of 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFCFFFE80F6B0D7D0542D23C" baseAuthorityName="Myers" baseAuthorityYear="1973" box="[525,790,1322,1348]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" genus="Advenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montisilvestris">
<emphasis id="60BBD714FFCFFFE80F6B0D7D0542D23C" box="[525,790,1322,1348]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="218">Advenus montisilvestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within the 
<taxonomicName id="95CF7085FFCFFFE80EF30D7D0215D23C" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1865" box="[917,1089,1322,1348]" class="Reptilia" family="Diploglossidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="17" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Diploglossidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
